overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the visual appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I began by conducting a thorough review of the
  existing design, identifying areas like the generic color palette, plain
  backgrounds, and basic form elements that needed refinement. The approach
  involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette, redesigning
  the main form layout with decorative elements and an improved progress
  indicator, and enhancing the welcome screen with feature cards. All core UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards were polished
  for a cohesive look. Crucially, I ensured consistent styling across all 14
  form sections, replacing old gray boxes with a more refined card-like design.
  During the review, a console error related to null input values was identified
  and fixed by modifying the  component to handle  gracefully. The
  outcome is a much more professional, cohesive, and aesthetically pleasing
  application tailored for a sleep health assessment.
